logodetection

Class StormVideoLogoDetector

  • java.lang.Object
    • logodetection.StormVideoLogoDetector

  • public class StormVideoLogoDetector
extends java.lang.Object
    This is a detector, which stores logo templates (LogoTemplate), and, given a patch of the frame, attempts to find a logo on it by matching it against each logo template. Logo templates are checked in order of their decreasing priority. They are stored in two separate lists: originalTemplates and addedTemplates. The first one contains static original logo templates, the second one, initially empty, contains dynamically added logo templates.

    ==============================Definitions==========================

    1. Query image, query logo, logo template - images of logos we are looking for.

    2. Train image, frame image - image of the frame in which we are looking for logos.

    3. Homography matrix, homography - 3x3 transformation matrix, which projects our logo template onto the frame space. Usually we project the corners of our template logo onto a frame to obtain the quadrilateral, which determines the locations of the detected logo.

    4. RoI, roi - region of interest. Usually this is a rectangle corresponding to the part of the image which we are examining.

    5. Original, Static logo templates - those that were added at the beginning.

    6. Added, Dynamic logo templates - those that were added during the detection.

    Usage:

    1. Initialize detector with original logo templates LogoTemplate. Also specify Parameters Parameters for detections such as parameters for SIFT feature extractor, RANSAC algorithm and others.

    2. Feed patches of the frames to the detector one by one using detectLogosInRoi(org.bytedeco.javacpp.opencv_core.Mat, org.bytedeco.javacpp.opencv_core.Rect)

    3. If detector detected some logo on the patch you can access its rectangle by getFoundRect(). If getFoundRect() returns null, then no logo has been detected on this patch.

    4. If you wish to add a new logo template (for example, you extracted a template from some frame), you should call addTemplate(tool.Serializable.PatchIdentifier, tool.Serializable.Mat).

    5. Also you may want to increment the priority of the existing logo template. Then you call incrementPriority(tool.Serializable.PatchIdentifier, int).

    See Also:
    LogoTemplate, RobustMatcher
